   25     b->size = 0;
   26     return b;           /* hand the partially-initialised blob back */
   27 }
   ```
   
   **GLOBAL FIX:**
   Implement a better error handling pattern to ensure resource management is
   more robust. Use a boolean flag or an enum to track the initialization state
   of the struct's members. This will prevent invalid operations on resources
   that cannot be tracked with `NULL` checks alone. Another approach is using
   smart pointers or resource-managing classes in languages like C++ to ensure
   automatic deallocation without double frees.
